Demonic Leviathan Form of Valtharix
Upon completing the modified Leviathan ritual in the Oceanic Expanse with the help of the Leviathan Civilization, Valtharix gains the ability to transform into a Demonic Leviathan, a truly terrifying and mighty form. This new power fuses his demonic essence with the primordial, abyssal energy of the Leviathans, creating a monstrous being of darkness and power that only fully manifests in the Abyssal Aquasphere and the Oceanic Expanse.
________________________________________
Demonic Leviathan Appearance (When Transformed):
â€¢	Size and Shape: Valtharixs body grows to an immense, towering sizeâ€”his form now rivals the largest of the Leviathan kin. His body is a massive fusion of infernal muscle and ancient aquatic magic, resembling a gargantuan, aquatic demon of abyssal horrors. His body flows like liquid stone, a serpentine titan that ripples with boundless energy.
â€¢	Scales: His once-black, obsidian skin becomes jagged and angular, covered in glistening, infernal scales that shimmer with deep oceanic blues, fiery reds, and iridescent whites. His scales are razor-sharp, like a combination of volcanic rock and coral, allowing him to tear through his enemies or crush his surroundings.
â€¢	Eyes: His eyes glow with a violent, pulsating energyâ€”fiery, shifting between molten red and abyssal blue. They exude an unnatural brilliance, giving him an unnerving gaze that can pierce through the darkest depths of the ocean.
â€¢	Horns: Long, twisted horns curve backward from his head, resembling the ancient spires of forgotten temples submerged deep beneath the waves. These horns are jagged and filled with cracks where glowing magma leaks, adding an infernal touch to his otherwise oceanic appearance.
â€¢	Tail and Fins: His tail is long and mighty, ending in a barbed, whip-like point capable of crushing ships or impaling multiple foes at once. He also has massive, spiny fins that extend from his back down to his tail, each of them glowing with swirling abyssal power. These fins can also slice through any who dare come too close, like razor-sharp blades made of water and infernal fire.
â€¢	Claws and Teeth: His claws elongate, becoming razor-sharp, resembling massive talons forged from the deepest oceanic abyss and the darkest pits of the Abyss. His teeth grow long and jagged, each one dripping with venomous energy capable of draining the very life force of anything they pierce.
â€¢	Wings: Unlike most leviathans, Valtharixâ€™s wings are vast and membranous, with a blackened, shark-skin-like texture. They span wide enough to create a storm as he flies, casting dark shadows over the sea below. They are not for flight in the traditional sense but for controlling the elements and generating devastating whirlpools, storms, and tidal waves.
â€¢	Aura: A constant whirl of infernal, abyssal, and oceanic energy surrounds Valtharix. His presence warps the very air and sea around himâ€”oceans part, winds howl, and the very fabric of reality seems to twist in his vicinity. This aura crushes the will of lesser beings, forcing them into submission or madness.
________________________________________
Abilities in Demonic Leviathan Form:
1.	Abyssal Tempest: Valtharix can summon massive storm systems in a 30-foot radius around him. These storms are filled with infernal lightning, violent waves of corrupted water, and poisonous mists that choke the life out of those trapped inside. Creatures within the storm take 6d10 lightning damage, or half on a successful DC 25 Dexterity saving throw. The storm lasts for 1 minute.
2.	Tidal Surge: Once per turn, Valtharix can summon an immense tidal wave that floods the area in front of him, pushing creatures back and dealing 4d10 bludgeoning damage to any creature caught in the wave. Those who fail a DC 25 Strength saving throw are knocked prone and pushed back 20 feet.
3.	Corrupted Abyssal Breath: Valtharix exhales a torrent of crushing water and infernal fire in a 60-foot cone. Creatures within the cone must make a DC 25 Constitution saving throw, taking 8d6 fire damage and 8d6 cold damage on a failed save, or half as much on a success. The area affected is left as difficult terrain due to the boiling, infernal waters.
4.	Leviathanâ€™s Wrath: Valtharix channels the power of the Leviathan, causing his claws to glow with fiery energy. His next melee attack deals an additional 6d6 fire damage, and if the target is a creature, they must succeed on a DC 25 Constitution saving throw or be stunned for 1 round.
5.	Abyssal Regeneration: While in this form, Valtharix regenerates 20 hit points at the start of each of his turns, and his resistance to damage types such as fire, lightning, and cold increases by 50%.
6.	Demonic Leviathans Roar: Once every 30 minutes, Valtharix can unleash a roar that reverberates through the waters, causing creatures within 300 feet to make a DC 25 Wisdom saving throw. On a failure, they are frightened for 1 minute. If they fail by 5 or more, they are paralyzed with fear for 1 minute instead.
7.	Abyssal Dominion: Valtharix can control sea creatures, including massive leviathan-like beasts. Once per day, he can call forth 1d4 colossal beasts that will aid him in battle or perform tasks on his command. These creatures are fiercely loyal, though they are bound by his will for only an hour.
8.	Void Rift: Valtharix can create an enormous tear in reality, pulling enemies within a 30-foot radius into the rift. Enemies must make a DC 25 Strength saving throw, or they are transported to a plane of nothingness for 1d10 minutes, leaving them vulnerable to instant death upon the riftâ€™s closing. This ability can be used 3 times per day.
