Server Lore 

In The Beginning, 

Before all of the realms were created, there was a group of entities (Dragons, gods, creatures, etc) that were the most powerful and they all decided to go and create realties (DND, This Minecraft Server, etc) and then once all of these realms were created people were created and allowed to live and do whatever they wanted. There was one person who was an exceptionally powerful magic wielder who we refer to as â€œThe Originalâ€ due to no-one knowing his name. This person eventually died but when he did the creators decided to split him and send him to many, if not all, of the realties. Each one of these splits has a full soul but each soul mirrors a certain aspect of â€œThe Original.â€. Draconic-souls usually mirror his aspect of strength and power. (Have to add more). Yet there is only one Demon-soul (Valtharix) who is the strongest of them all and represents the aspect of raw unrefined potent magic and raw power. Each one of these mirror-souls know that they are a mirror and may tell others about this if they wish. There are rules, mirror-souls must follow: 

A mirror-soul knows another mirror-soul if they ever see one; This implies that mirror-souls can sense if you are one or if you try to disguise as one 

A mirror-soul cannot harm in any way, another mirror-soul or their friends 

Acts as an exception to Rule 2. If a duel or other thing happens with ways to stop fatal wounds, Rule 2 is null and void for the duration of the duel, fight, etcâ€¦l, 

Server Phases 

Phase 0(Server Start) 

At the start of the server, I explain how this server is magical and some of the lore will be told to them. I tell them how there are structures in the dimensions that contain pieces of the lore of this server and donâ€™t take the pieces of lore out of the structures. 

At the end of the first week of the server, everyone decides who they side with, and which dimension they side with. If someone chooses a dimension other than the overworld they get teleported there. This event ends Phase 0 and begins Phase 1. 

Phase 1 

Once Phase 1 begins, some factions should start fighting lightly. And the factions should reach out to the players for alliances.  

