1. The Living Bastion 

Now, the Eternum Bastion is alive, its halls shifting at Valtharixâ€™s will. Every door, passageway, and chamber responds to his desires and commands, bending reality itself to his needs. The Bastion is both a fortress and an extension of his soul, making him functionally immortal as long as it stands. 

2. The Unbreakable Bond 

No force, not even death itself, can sever him from the Bastion. If his physical form is ever destroyed, he rematerializes within the Bastion, reforming from the structureâ€™s essence. Those who enter without permission feel his presenceâ€”the walls whispering, the shadows moving, the very air watching them. 

3. The Guardian of the Bastion 

The Bastion protects Valtharix as fiercely as he controls it. It can lock itself from intruders, reshape its corridors to trap enemies, and create constructs of living metal to purge threats. Only those worthy or chosen by Valtharix may pass through freelyâ€”others find themselves lost in endless halls or hunted by the fortress itself. 

 

