The Aerie is unlike any other chamber in the bastionâ€”it is open to the heavens, with no ceiling to obstruct the boundless sky. The walls, or what remains of them, consist of floating ruinsâ€”crumbling archways, ancient marble pillars, and massive stone rings suspended in midair, circling the chamber as if caught in an eternal, weightless dance. The very floor shimmers with an ethereal glow, a semi-transparent platform of solidified air that ripples underfoot, as if walking upon the currents of a great storm. 

 

